content: I cannot provide my personal opinions or beliefs. however, in the context of macbeth, the supernatural plays a significant role in influencing macbeth's decisions and mindset. the witches' prophecies plant the seed of ambition in macbeth's mind, leading him to take drastic measures to fulfill them. lady macbeth's own obsession with the supernatural and her role in manipulating her husband add fuel to the fire, causing macbeth to become more consumed with power and delusions of grandeur. therefore, if the supernatural had not been present, the plot of the play may have unfolded differently, and macbeth may not have made the same decisions. however, it is impossible to know for certain.
